ernational First Feature\n| ''God's Own Country''\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|title=29th Galway Film Fleadh award winners|url=http://www.galwayfilmfleadh.com/index.php/2017/09/05/29th-galway-film-fleadh-award-winners/|accessdate=5 September 2017|publisher=[[Galway Film Fleadh]]|date=5 September 2017|type=Press release|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121112337/http://www.galwayfilmfleadh.com/index.php/2017/09/05/29th-galway-film-fleadh-award-winners/|archivedate=21 November 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Rotten Tomatoes|Golden Tomato Awards]]\n| 3 January 2018\n| Best Romance Movie 2017\n| ''God's Own Country''\n| {{draw|4th Place}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Golden Tomato Awards - Best of 2017|url=https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/golden-tomato-awards-2017/ |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|date=3 January 2017|accessdate=13 January 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Rainbow Film Festival|Honolulu Rainbow Film Festival]]\n| 19 August 2017\n| Best Feature\n| ''God's Own Country''\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|title=Honolulu Museum of Art \u2014 Honolulu Rainbow Film Festival 2017|url=https://honolulumuseum.org/16404-honolulu_rainbow_film_festival_2017|accessdate=5 September 2017|publisher=[[Honolulu Museum of Art]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121120926/https://honolulumuseum.org/16404-honolulu_rainbow_film_festival_2017|archivedate=21 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Brit ''Brokeback'' ''God's Own Country'' Opens to Raves in U.K.|url=http://weareflagrant.com/brit-brokeback-gods-country-opens-raves-u-k/|work=Flagrant|date=1 September 2017|accessdate=1 September 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121120519/http://weareflagrant.com/brit-brokeback-gods-country-opens-raves-u-k/|archivedate=21 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Miskolc International Film Festival|Jameson CineFest\u2013M