 Country'' wins Edinburgh Film Festival award|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-edinburgh-east-fife-40454745|accessdate=30 June 2017|publisher=BBC|date=30 June 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\"| [[Empire Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 18 March 2018\n| [[Empire Award for Best British Film|Best British Film]]\n| ''{{sort|God's|God's Own Country}}''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/empire-film-awards-2018-the-last-jedi-leads-the-pack-with-nine-nominations-including-best-film-a3744171.html |title=Empire Film Awards 2018: ''The Last Jedi'' leads the pack with nine nominations including Best Actress for Daisy Ridley |first=Jennifer |last=Ruby |publisher=[[London Evening Standard]] |date=19 January 2018 |accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref><br/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/star-wars-last-jedi-leads-nominations-uks-empire-awards-1076867 |title=''Star Wars: The Last Jedi'' Leads Nominations for U.K.'s Empire Awards |first=Alex |last=Ritman |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=22 January 2018 |accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Empire Award for Best Male Newcomer|Best Male Newcomer]]\n| [[Josh O'Connor]] \n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Screenplay\n| Francis Lee\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"5\"| [[Evening Standard British Film Awards]]\n|rowspan=\"5\"| 8 February 2018\n| Best Film\n| ''{{sort|God's|God's Own Country}}''\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/go/london/film/discover-all-the-nominations-for-this-years-evening-standard-british-film-awards-a3738446.html|title=Discover all the nominations for this year's ''Evening Standard'' British Film Awards |work=[[London Evening Standard]] |date=12 January 2018|accessdate=12 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actor\n| {{sort|Hart|Ian Hart}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actress\n| {{sort|Jones|Gemma Jones}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\" | Breakthrough of the Year\n| {{sort|Lee|Francis Lee}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| {{sort|O'Connor|Josh O'Connor}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Frameline Film Festival|Frameline San Francisco International LGBTQ Film Festival]]\n| 27 June 2017\n| AT&T Audience Award\n| ''God's Own Country''\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|title=Frameline41 Awards Announced|url=https://www.frameline.org/year-round/frameline-blog/frameline41-awards|accessdate= 27 June 2017|publisher=Frameline San Francisco International LGBTQ Film Festival|date=27 June 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170829163050/https://www.frameline.org/year-round/frameline-blog/frameline41-awards|archivedate=29 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| F\u00fcnf Seen Film Festival\n| 5 August 2017\n| Audience Award\n| ''God's Own Country''\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|title=F\u00fcnf Seen Film Festival \u2013 Publikumspreis|url=http://www.breitwand.com/home/cm/fff-current-sektion/3/index.html|accessdate=27 June 2017|publisher=F\u00fcnf Seen Film Festival|date=27 June 2017|language=German|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121093635/http://www.breitwand.com/home/cm/fff-current-sektion/3/index.html|archivedate=21 November 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Galway Film Fleadh]]\n| 5 September 2017\n| Best International First Feature\n| ''God's Own Country''\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|title=29th Galway Film Fleadh award winners|url=http://www.galwayfilmfleadh.com/index.php/2017/09/05/29th-galway-film-fleadh-award-winners/|accessdate=5 September 2017|publisher=[[Galway Film Fleadh]]|date=5 September 2017|type=Press release|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121112337/http://www.galwayfilmfleadh.com/index.php/2017/09/05/29th-galway-film-fleadh-award-winners/|archivedate=21 November 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Rotten Tomatoes|Golden Tomato Awards]]\n| 3 January 2018\n| Best Romance Movie 2017\n| ''God's Own Country''\n| {{draw|4th Place}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|title=Golden Tomato Awards - Best of 2017|url=https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/golden-tomato-awards-2017/ |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|date=3 January 2017|accessdate=13 January 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Rainbow Film Festival|Honolulu Rainbow Film Festival]]\n| 19 August 2017\n| Best Feature\n| ''God's Own Country''\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|title=Honolulu Museum of Art \u2014 Honolulu Rainbow Film Festival 2017|url=https://honolulumuseum.org/16404-honolulu_rainbow_film_festival_2017|accessdate=5 September 2017|publisher=[[Honolulu Museum of Art]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121120926/https://honolulumuseum.org/16404-honolulu_rainbow_film_festival_2017|archivedate=21 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Brit ''Brokeback'' ''God's Own Country'' Opens to Raves in U.K.|url=http://weareflagrant.com/brit-brokeback-gods-country-opens-raves-u-k/|work=Flagrant|date=1 September 2017|accessdate=1 September 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121120519/http://weareflagrant.com/brit-brokeback-gods-country-opens-raves-u-k/|archivedate=21 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Miskolc International Film Festival|Jameson CineFest\u2013Miskolc International Film Festival]]\n| 17 September 2017\n| Emeric Pressburger Prize\n| ''God's Own Country''\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|title=Jameson CineFest 2017 International Competition|url=https://www.cinefest.hu/eng/versenyfilmek_eng.html|accessdate=5 September 2017|publisher=Jameson CineFest\u2013Miskolc International Film Festival|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171121122356/https://www.cinefest.hu/eng/versenyfilmek_eng.html|archivedate=21 November 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"5\"| 